  "prompt": "What are the top 10 books one must read before turning 20 something?",
  "response": "Here are 10 must-read books for young adults before turning 20:\n\n1. \"To Kill a Mockingbird\" by Harper Lee\n- Classic novel about racial injustice and moral growth\n- Teaches empathy and social consciousness\n\n2. \"1984\" by George Orwell\n- Dystopian novel exploring government control and individual freedom\n- Develops critical thinking about societal structures\n\n3. \"The Alchemist\" by Paulo Coelho\n- Inspirational story about following one's dreams\n- Teaches personal philosophy and life purpose\n\n4. \"Brave New World\" by Aldous Huxley\n- Thought-provoking exploration of technology and society\n- Challenges perspectives on human progress\n\n5. \"Man's Search for Meaning\" by Viktor Frankl\n- Personal account of survival during Holocaust\n- Provides profound insights into human resilience and purpose\n\n6. \"The Catcher in the Rye\" by J.D. Salinger\n- Coming-of-age novel about teenage alienation\n- Resonates with young adult experiences\n\n7. \"Thinking, Fast and Slow\" by Daniel Kahneman\n- Explores human decision-making processes\n- Develops understanding of personal psychology\n\n8. \"The Power of Habit\" by Charles Duhigg\n- Explains habit formation and personal transformation\n- Provides practical self-improvement strategies\n\n9. \"Rich Dad Poor Dad\" by Robert Kiyosaki\n- Financial education and mindset development\n- Teaches fundamental principles of wealth creation\n\n10. \"Sapiens\" by Yuval Noah Harari\n- Comprehensive human history\n- Offers broader perspective on human civilization",
